parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to increased risk of injury or death in the event of an accident, as the airbags may not deploy properly or at all.
symptoms: the driver-side airbag does not deploy in a crash
the side curtain airbags deploy incorrectly
the airbag system fails to function properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The fracture and dislodging of the spare tire mounting support can cause the spare tire to fall off the vehicle, potentially causing injury or damage to other vehicles on the road.
symptoms: the spare tire mounting support is fractured
the spare tire is loose or detached.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The premature peeling of paint on the hood and roof can lead to rust and corrosion, compromising the structural integrity of the vehicle and potentially causing safety issues.
symptoms: rust or corrosion on the hood and roof.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The random stalling of the engine can cause loss of power and control, increasing the risk of accidents, especially when accelerating from a stop or navigating through intersections.
symptoms: often when accelerating from a stop light or stop sign
the vehicle will restart when put in neutral and the key is turned back over
the engine may stall once a week or multiple times a week
or may not stall for several weeks
